*Network MGMT*

ip a -> shows ip and interfaces

ifconfig -> same

hostname -I -> shows ip

sudo ip link set Interface_Name down

sudo ip link set Interface_Name up

sudo ip link set Interface_Name name New_Name

iwconfig -> displays and manages wireless interface settings

sudo systemctl restart NetworkManager -> restarts the NetworkManager service to refresh network connections and fix connectivity issues

nmcli device wifi connect 'Wifi_Name' password 'password' -> to connect to a wifi

nmcli device wifi list -> lists wifi connections near you

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

*Apache2*

sudo apt install apache2
sudo systemctl start Apache2
sudo systemctl status Apache2
sudo systemctl stop Apache2
sudo systemctl restart Apache2

-> you can use apache2 on bridge to see it on your other devices
 
-> /var/www/html
-> here you can change index.html
-> /etc/apache2/ports.conf
-> here you can change port number for apache2
-> /var/logs/apache2
-> Here you can check logs 
*SSH*
sudo apt install ssh
sudo systemctl start ssh
sudo systemctl status ssh
sudo systemctl stop ssh
sudo systemctl restart ssh
on other device terminal
->ssh username@ip-address
->Then yes
->password
/etc/ssh/sshd_config
-> here you can change port number
-> PermitRootLogin yes -> To Allow Root User Login
sudo netdiscover -r ip-address/subnet  -> shows devices connected to same network
ss -tulnp -> show active ports 
bridge -> you can connect to all the devices that are connected with your router
NAT -> connect to only host
